Randall:<br><br>
I understand your point of view.<br><br>
I experienced your description of bias when I was in the 7th and 8th grades in the late 50's in the south. I had two years of the Civil War from a southern point of view. My roots were from NYC, and much of what was said there with enthusiasm was lost on me.<br><br>
I have since developed a different perspective on the Civil War, and other topics as well. My perspective on the Vietnam War is changing as I explore my roots in the war and subsequent events. This PBS point of view forum has indeed served as a catalyst for continuing exploration. I am beginning to clearly discriminate in my mind the &quot;official line&quot; from the reality. If I can do this, so can others, I believe, even many years from now.<br><br>
My grandfather was a NYC Police Officer, and through his teachings I find am well grounded in the reality of human <br>
nature. I feel there will always be some around with the capacity to discern.<br><br>
We agree, therefore, to disagree on a very fine point. <br><br>
Regards,<br><br>
